    keyIdeas: ['Scientific theories should take empirical risks that make failure informative.', 'Corroboration records performance under testing without turning evidence into final proof or probability of truth.', 'Open institutions improve political judgment by enabling criticism, accountability, and nonviolent correction.'],
    keyWorks: ['The Logic of Scientific Discovery', 'The Poverty of Historicism', 'The Open Society and Its Enemies', 'Conjectures and Refutations', 'Objective Knowledge', 'Postscript to The Logic of Scientific Discovery'],
